can be summarized by

274
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:01,440
a very simple idea

275
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:04,440
that there's a geometry

276
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:07,440
of space-time

277
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:10,440
and that geometry is determined

278
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,440
by knowing the distance between

279
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:16,440
every pair of neighboring space-time points.

280
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,440
This is a fact about geometry in general,

281
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:21,440
about Riemannian geometry in general,

282
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,440
that if you know the distance between

283
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,440
every pair of neighboring space-time points,

284
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:28,440
that in principle you can reconstruct

285
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,440
the entire geometry of space.

286
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:36,440
I'll give you an example in a few minutes.

287
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:40,440
But of a non-trivial geometry.

288
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,440
But you represent then

289
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:48,440
the small interval between two points

290
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:51,440
by a coordinate, a set of coordinates,

291
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,440
we can call them x mu,

292
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:55,440
where as usual, mu runs from 0 to 3,

293
00:13:55,440 --> 00:14:00,440
and another point, x mu plus dx mu,

294
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,440
where this little interval is called dx mu.

295
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:06,440
What's the distance between those two points?

296
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:09,440
The distance between those two points,

297
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,440
of course, it is whatever it is,

298
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:14,440
it's a certain space-time interval there,

299
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,440
but how do you represent it

300
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:19,440
in terms of the coordinates of those points?

301
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,440
In general relativity, we wrote that

302
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:24,440
the distance between those two points, ds squared,

303
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:29,440
is equal to dt squared minus dx squared

304
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:33,440
minus dy squared minus dz squared,

305
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,440
which we can also write as

306
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:39,440
dx mu dx mu.

307
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,440
And another way that we wrote it

308
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:45,440
was eta mu nu,

309
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:49,440
dx mu dx nu,

310
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:52,440
where eta was just a matrix,

311
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,440
a very simple matrix,

312
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:57,440
oh, did we call this tau, proper time?

313
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,440
Maybe we called it tau, proper time.

314
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:04,440
Where eta,

315
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,440
eta was just a matrix,

316
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:11,440
1, minus 1, minus 1, minus 1, 0s everywhere else.

317
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,440
Those are three ways that we wrote

318
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:17,440
the space-time interval between neighboring points.

319
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:22,440
Now, one statement of the general theory,

320
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:24,440
of the special theory of relativity,

321
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:26,440
excuse me, the special theory of relativity,

322
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:29,440
is that the tau squared

323
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:32,440
should be taken to be an invariant of the geometry,

324
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:34,440
in other words,

325
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,440
that all observers,

326
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:39,440
generally they will not agree

327
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:41,440
on what dx is.

328
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,440
If we rotate coordinates,

329
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,440
or Lorentz transform coordinates,

330
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:49,440
they'll disagree about the components of dx,

331
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,440
but what they will agree about

332
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:55,440
is the proper time between the two points.

333
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:58,440
So the proper time is an invariant.

334
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:04,440
That's one initial starting point

335
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,440
for a sort of axiomatic description

336
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:09,440
of special theory of relativity.

337
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,440
The second statement,

338
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:14,440
which is not an axiom, it's a theorem,

339
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:18,440
is that the transformations

340
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:22,440
that you can do on x, y, z, and t,

341
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:27,440
which preserve the form of the interval,

342
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:30,440
are Lorentz transformations.

343
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,440
If we look at Lorentz transformations,

344
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,440
and rotations, and so forth,

345
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:36,440
the interval in terms of primed coordinates

346
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,440
has exactly the same form as the interval

347
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:41,440
in terms of the unprimed coordinates.

348
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:44,440
So that's a statement of symmetry

349
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,440
that the basic proper time

350
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:49,440
can be expressed

351
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:52,440
in all Lorentz frames

352
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,440
by the same basic formula.

353
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,440
And then the final statement is

354
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:59,440
that having found what the symmetry

355
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,440
of the interval is,

356
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,440
having found out

357
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:04,440
what the symmetry of the,

358
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,440
what family of coordinates

359
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:09,440
always gives the same answer here

360
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:11,440
for the interval,

361
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,440
then the rule is

362
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,440
all laws of physics

363
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,440
are identical

364
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,440
in those different frames of reference

365
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:22,440
which are related by Lorentz transformations.

366
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:25,440
Now, of course, it is not true

367
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,440
that every set of coordinates

368
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:29,440
that you could think of,

369
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,440
the interval is expressed in the same way.

370
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,440
Let me give you an example

371
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,440
just from ordinary space.

372
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:38,440
Not space-time, but space.

373
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:41,440
If I take coordinates x and y,

374
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:44,440
which are the usual kind of,

375
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,440
sorry, x and y,

376
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:49,440
the usual kind of Cartesian coordinates,

377
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:52,440
then yes, the separation between two points

378
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:55,440
is just the x squared plus the y squared.

379
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:58,440
If I rotate the coordinates

380
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,440
to x prime and y prime,

381
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:04,440
by a standard rotation of coordinates,

382
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:06,440
then the same interval

383
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:10,440
is dx prime squared plus dy prime squared.

384
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,440
But what if I do something dumb?

385
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:15,440
Like, use coordinates,

386
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:18,440
use a coordinate mesh,

387
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,440
where x and y

388
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:23,440
are not measured in the same units.

389
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,440
x is measured in inches,

390
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:29,440
and y is measured in meters.

391
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:32,440
I have a point x, y,

392
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:35,440
and a point x plus dx,

393
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:37,440
and y plus dy.

394
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,440
What is the distance between those two points?

395
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,440
It is not dx squared plus dy squared.

396
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,440
Why not?

397
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:46,440
Because you're measuring the interval

398
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:49,440
in different units.

399
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,440
In particular, supposing I wanted

400
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,440
the distance in inches.

401
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:57,440
Let's see, let me use centimeters here.

402
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:00,440
Centimeters and meters.

403
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,440
Centimeters and meters.

404
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,440
I don't like factors of 12

405
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,440
and factors of 144,

406
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,440
factors of 10 are easier.

407
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:12,440
Supposing I want the distance

408
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,440
between neighboring points,

409
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,440
but I want to measure it in centimeters.

410
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:18,440
In centimeters.

411
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:20,440
This is x, and this is y.

412
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,440
What is the distance between two points?

413
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:26,440
It is not dx squared plus dy squared.

414
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:30,940
But it is dx squared

415
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:35,440
plus dy divided by 100 squared.

416
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,440
Why over 100?

417
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,940
Well, it is obvious that

418
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:40,440
if you use the same unit

419
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,440
for y as for x,

420
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,440
and you're measuring things in centimeters,

421
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:47,440
then it would be dx squared plus dy squared.

422
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:51,440
But if I use meters for the vertical axis here,

423
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,440
and I want to get back to centimeters,

424
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:55,440
I'd better divide

425
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:58,440
the y component of vectors by 100.

426
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,440
So we can rewrite this then.

427
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,440
It's dx squared

428
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:04,440
plus

429
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,440
1 over 100 squared.

430
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,440
1 over 10,000

431
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,440
dy squared.

432
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,440
So if I do something stupid,

433
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:14,440
like use awkward coordinates

434
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,440
in where x and y are not measured

435
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,440
in the same units,

436
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,440
then my expression for distance

437
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,440
is going to have a form

438
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,440
which will contain

439
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,440
some funny numbers in it,

440
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,440
like 1 over 100,

441
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,440
10,000 here.

442
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,440
In particular, it won't be the nice symmetric

443
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,440
dx squared plus dy squared.

444
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,440
I go a little further.

445
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:37,440
Supposing I don't use

446
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,440
orthogonal coordinates.

447
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,440
Supposing I decide to choose

448
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,440
coordinates in the following way.

449
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:46,440
I choose coordinate axes which look like that.

450
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:49,440
And now my rule is going to be

451
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:52,440
the coordinates of a point are gotten

452
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,440
by moving along the x-axis

453
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,440
not to the point where you drop a perpendicular,

454
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:59,440
but where you draw a line

455
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,440
parallel to the y-axis.

456
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,440
Likewise, the y-coordinate,

457
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:05,440
so this would be the x-coordinate

458
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,440
and this would be the y-coordinate.

459
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,440
Then,

460
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,440
the distance between two points,

461
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:13,440
you don't have the standard

462
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,440
Pythagorean theorem anymore.

463
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,440
We have triangles, we have triangles now.

464
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,440
Here's x,

465
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,440
here's y.

466
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,440
This is not a right triangle.

467
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,440
So, the hypotenuse is not a hypotenuse.

468
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,440
It's just a third side of a triangle.

469
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:29,440
The length of this is definitely not

470
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:31,440
the x squared plus the y squared.

471
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,440
Even if we use the same units

472
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:35,440
on the x and y-axis,

473
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,440
it's just not true.

474
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:39,440
What is it?

475
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,440
Well, I won't write down

476
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,440
precisely what the formula is.

477
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,440
But it will always be of the form

478
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,440
of some kind of a triangle.

479
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,440
And that's what I'm going to do.

480
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:51,440
I'm going to write down

481
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,440
the length of the triangle.

482
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,440
The length of the triangle

483
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:57,440
is one coefficient of the x squared

484
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,440
plus another coefficient of the y squared.

485
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:01,440
Let me not call it d.

486
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,440
Let's call it a, b, and c.

487
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,440
a

488
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,440
some number b

489
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,440
the y squared

490
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,440
but then

491
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,440
what's new about

492
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:15,440
coordinate systems which have

493
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,440
angles in them like this

494
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,440
which are not rectangular

495
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,440
which are not perpendicular

496
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,440
is that there are additional terms

497
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:25,440
c times dxdy

498
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,440
products

499
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,440
of different

500
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,440
coordinates

501
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:33,440
that's what happens

502
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,440
if you have

503
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:37,440
coordinate systems

504
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,440
which are not orthogonal

505
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,440
which are not orthogonal coordinates

506
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,440
off diagonal elements like that

507
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:45,440
you can also write this

508
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,440
in another way

509
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,440
you can write it c over 2 times dxdy

510
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,440
plus c over 2

511
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,440
times dy dx.

512
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:57,440
And so you have a whole bunch of

513
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,440
coefficients.

514
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:01,440
We could give these coefficients names

515
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,440
we could call this

516
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:07,440
for the fact that it multiplies dx squared

517
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:09,440
we could call this 2, 2

518
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,440
well let's not

519
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:13,440
why are we giving them different names

520
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:15,440
we could just call it a, 2, 2

521
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:17,440
or a, y, y

522
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:19,440
this one

523
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,440
we could call a, x, y

524
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:23,440
and this one

525
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,440
we could call a, y, x

526
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,440
notice that a, x, y

527
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,440
and a, y, x are exactly the same thing

528
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,440
I simply took the coefficient

529
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:35,440
of dxdy and split it

530
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:37,440
between two terms

531
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:39,440
one which is dxdy and the other

532
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:41,440
which is dy dx just to symmetrize it

533
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,440
just to make it nice and symmetric

534
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:45,440
finally

535
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,440
I could display these coefficients

536
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,440
a as a matrix

537
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:51,440
a, 1, 1

538
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,440
a, 1, well

539
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:55,440
x, y, 1, 2

540
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:59,440
a, 1, 2

541
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:01,440
a, 2, 1

542
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,440
a, 2, 2

543
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,440
just display them as a metric

544
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,440
as a matrix

545
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:09,440
in fact the matrix is called a metric

546
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:11,440
and

547
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:13,440
this metric

548
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,440
completely encapsulates

549
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,440
what the

550
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:19,440
distance between neighboring pairs

551
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:21,440
of points is

552
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,440
and what the coefficients are

553
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,440
in terms of four coefficients

554
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,440
laid out as a matrix

555
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,440
this matrix is called the metric

556
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,440
now

557
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,440
if we're dealing with ordinary

558
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:35,440
space of the blackboard

559
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,440
flat space, uniform space

560
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:39,440
everywhere the same

561
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,440
and

562
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:43,440
